cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use CritterGym in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "CritterGym: A Procedurally-Generated Creature-Collection Benchmark for Measuring Long-Horizon Agency and Generalization"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Park"
    given-names: "Myungsoo"
repository-code: "https://github.com/anolysius/creature-rl-env"
url: "https://anolysius.github.io/creature-rl-env/"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - reinforcement-learning
  - benchmark
  - procedural-generation
  - generalization
  - evaluation
  - rlvr
abstract: >-
  A procedurally-generated creature-collection RL environment for benchmarking
  long-horizon agency, strategic hidden-rule inference, and generalization,
  with verifiable (RLVR) rewards, a train/test seed split, a parity-proven JAX
  port, and a contamination-proof regenerable sealed evaluation track. Built by
  a human-directed AI coding agent (Claude, Anthropic) with pre-registered
  measurement rules; see the in-repo technical report at docs/paper/.
